cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on operating systems (OS) and system-level issues, such as disk I/O scheduling policies. Therefore, cs.OS is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses system-level policies and parameters, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.PF (performance). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a policy specification API, which could be considered under the sub-category of cs.AR (hardware architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of EOS on Linux subsystems, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.PL (programming languages).
